paragraph.treatmentCitationGroup:
Adocimus bellus
Murray, 1664: 311


, t. 36, f. 5. Mysol (near “Ceram”);

caption.paragraph:
FIGURE 1.

Adocimus
(
Adocimus
) 
bellus

, orig. Specimens from Indonesian New Guinea; A, C–E: male, typical form (“Hatam, Doria”); H–J: male, typical form (“…Suma-Uam…”); B: female, unicolorous form (“… Hatam, Beccari, 1875”); K: female, typical form (“… Madang Dist., Finistrerre Mts…”); 
A
: body, male, dorsal (typical form); 
B
: body, female, dorsal (unicolorous form); C-K: typical form— 
C
: head, dorsal; 
D
: head and thorax, ventral; 
E
: lateral side of abdominal segments 5 and 6, dorsal; 
F
: apex of terminal abdominal segment of male with exposed serrate apex of anal sclerite, ventral; 
G
: apex of terminal abdominal segment of female with serrate apex of pygidium, ventral; 
H
: tegmen, ventral; 
I
: penis trunk, dorsal; 
J
: proximal part of inner sac with armature; 
K
: ovipositor, ventral. Scale bars: 
a
= 2.0 mm to Fig. A and 2.3 mm to Fig. B; 
b
= 1.0 mm to Figs C–E; 
с
= 0.5 mm to Figs F–K.
